Lockheed Martin Investment Management Company Lmimco

Senior Equity Research Analyst, Global Financials Sector
Req ID : 302489BR
Job Code/Title : E5734:Sr Analyst, Internal Equity
Job Description : Lockheed Martin Corporation headquartered in Bethesda, MD, Lockheed Martin (LMC) is a global security company that employs about 123,000 people worldwide and is principally engaged in the research, design, development, manufacture, integration and sustainment of advanced technology systems, products and services.
LM Investment Management Company
Lockheed Martin Investment Management Company ("LMIMCo"), established in 1997, is the named fiduciary for the investment of assets in Lockheed Martin sponsored pension, savings, and other employee benefit trusts. Our mission is to manage the assets entrusted to us with prudence, diligence, and skill. LMIMCo's obligation is to protect the interests of the benefit plan participants by enhancing the value of the assets. We operate solely in the interests of plan participants and beneficiaries, and with the care, skill, prudence, and diligence that a prudent individual acting in like capacity and familiar with such matters would use.

Our primary fiduciary responsibilities include the establishment of investment policies and strategies governing the investment of assets in various employee trust funds, and the appointment, removal, and monitoring of external investment managers and other service providers who exercise delegated authority over the investment and custody of trust Assets.
Position: The Senior Equity Research Analyst covering the Global Financial sector provides support to the LMIMCO internal equity team by researching the business fundamentals, earnings prospects, technical analysis and other stock drivers for companies in the LMIMCO universe, and making investment recommendations to the Managing Director of Global Equities (Portfolio Manager). The LMIMCO internal equity group currently manages an $800 Million US Large Cap equity portfolio and will launch a Global Large Cap equity portfolio January 2015.
Primary Responsibilities • Conduct industry and company specific comprehensive fundamental analysis, including in-depth financial statement analysis. 
• Actively monitor stock technicals, buy-side and sell-side sentiment, as well as intra-sector rotations. • Present overviews and timely investment recommendations to the equity team, including buy and sell ideas. • Identify company and industry trends. • Provide meaningful written research summaries. • Participate in and attend meetings and conferences with companies and analysts.
Basic Qualifications • 5-7 equity research experience covering the global financial sector (United States (U.S.) and pan-European financial sector equity research experience a must)
• Experience with United States (U.S.) and European (EU) equity markets
• Prior experience working closely with a Portfolio Manager.
• Strong Financial Analysis acumen
Desired skills • MBA & Chartered Financial Analyst certification is desired. • Equity research experience in covering the Asian financial sector. • Experience in Asian equity markets • Hedge fund experience. • Experience in actively following stocks and markets and making timely Buy and Sell recommendations. 
• Experience with hedge fund portfolios. • Must be quantitatively-oriented, self-motivated and have a strong sense of initiative. • Excellent interpersonal, written and oral communication skills. • Ability to work as a contributing member of a team. • Ability to adapt quickly and work well under pressure in a fast-paced, challenging environment. • Ability to work both independently and as a part of a research/investment team to identify potential opportunities and exploit inefficiencies in the marketplace.
Lockheed Martin is an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, protected veteran status, or disability status.
This is a preview of the Manager, Quantitative Programming and Analysis job at Lockheed Martin. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!
Job Description Manager, Quantitative Programming and Analysis

Lockheed Martin Corporation headquartered in Bethesda, MD, Lockheed Martin (LMC) is a global security company that employs about 123,000 people worldwide and is principally engaged in the research, design, development, manufacture, integration and sustainment of advanced technology systems, products and services.
The Manager, Quantitative Programming and Analysis, reporting to the Managing Director, Quantitative Research and Asset Allocation, will write computer programs to compute daily pension plan performance, conduct attribution analysis, monitor asset allocation and risk exposures. He/She also needs to write computer codes to do quantitative screening and analysis on risk/return characteristics on asset classes, sectors, and individual securities. In addition, the manager will help to conduct back-testing on various investment strategies.
The analyst’s responsibilities will include but not limit to:
• Modify and improve investment performance system
• Write computer codes to implement performance measurement and attribution analytics

• Conduct asset allocation and risk analysis
• Write computer programs to monitor and analyze investment portfolio holding exposures
• Quantitative screening on risk/returns for different assets, sectors, and individual securities
• Conduct back-testing for various strategies
• Special projects, etc.
Basic Qualifications Required Skills
• Solid computer programming skills
• Deep understanding on modern portfolio theories and rich working experience on investment performance analytics
• Working knowledge on equity, fixed-income, commodity, hedge fund, private equity, real estate, etc. and familiarity with derivatives
• Demonstrated persistence to see projects through completion
• System development experience and strong technical skills, including VBA programming, MATLAB, Perl, Java, etc.
• 3+ years working experience in investment industry
• Bachelor degree in quantitative sciences, such as mathematics, physics, engineering, computer science
Desired skills CFA preferred




 


















